 <entry>
   <title>Backup MySQL database to Amazon S3</title>
   <link href="/mysql-amazon-s3-backup"/>
   <updated>2016-07-04T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
   <id>/mysql-amazon-s3-backup</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;h1 id=&quot;repository&quot;&gt;Repository&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The setup and usage is quite simple. Just follow the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;README.md&lt;/code&gt; at &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/avinashjoshi/MySQL-AmazonS3-Backup&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;http://github.com/avinashjoshi/MySQL-AmazonS3-Backup&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&quot;background&quot;&gt;Background&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recently, I was wondering about a good way to backup my MySQL databases to some place that is safe, reliable and easily accessible and not in the same server where my code is hosted. By now I have had some experience with Amazon Web Services (AWS). They are so easy to work with!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Initially I was using my dedicated hosting provider’s default backup service. Problem? I have no idea where my backup is and in case of emergency, there would be some latency. So, I wrote a quick script that uses &lt;a href=&quot;https://aws.amazon.com/cli/&quot;&gt;AWS Command Line Interface (CLI)&lt;/a&gt; to backup!&lt;/p&gt;

</content>
 </entry>
 
 <entry>
   <title>Modifying config / file in vendor project (via composer)</title>
   <link href="/modifying-config-file-in-composer-vendor"/>
   <updated>2016-02-25T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
   <id>/modifying-config-file-in-composer-vendor</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Let me start by saying that I understand - its not a good idea / practice to change vendor files.
But there are situations, where this cannot be avoided!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recently when using &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mpdf1.com/mpdf/index.php&quot;&gt;mPDF&lt;/a&gt; package with &lt;a href=&quot;http://cakephp.org&quot;&gt;CakePHP&lt;/a&gt;
via &lt;a href=&quot;http://getcomposer.org&quot;&gt;composer&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mpdf/mpdf&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mpdf/mpdf&lt;/a&gt;,
I needed to touch one of the config files in the package
- specifically the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;config_fonts.php&lt;/code&gt; as there was a need to change or add default fonts&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:mpdf-change-font&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:mpdf-change-font&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; when generating pdf.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;one-solution&quot;&gt;One solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One solution is to manually download the package and add it to your “Library” folder. This will unfortunately increase the size of your codebase!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;my-solution&quot;&gt;My Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can leverage the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;post-autoload-dump&lt;/code&gt; event in composer&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:post-autoload-dump&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:post-autoload-dump&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; to generate / overwrite the config file (after first backing up the original file)!
The only thing to be maintained in our repository was the config file to be overwritten.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I created a &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;postAutoloadDump()&lt;/code&gt; static function inside my &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Install&lt;/code&gt; class and added that to the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;post-autoload-dump&lt;/code&gt; event in &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;composer.json&lt;/code&gt;.
Here is a very basic CakePHP code (similar method can be used for any generic php project):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;file-srcconsoleinstallerphp&quot;&gt;file: &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;src/Console/Installer.php&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-php&quot; data-lang=&quot;php&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cp&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;?php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;#### truncated_code ####
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nc&quot;&gt;Installer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;postAutoloadDump&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;Event&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$event&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$config&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$event&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;na&quot;&gt;getComposer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;na&quot;&gt;getConfig&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$vendorDir&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;realpath&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$config&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;na&quot;&gt;get&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;vendor-dir&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;));&lt;/span&gt;

        &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$originalFile&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$vendorDir&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;/mpdf/mpdf/config_fonts.php&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$backupFile&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$vendorDir&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;/mpdf/mpdf/config_fonts-orig.php&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$customFontFile&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;dirname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nx&quot;&gt;__DIR__&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&#39;/../config/for_mpdf/config_fonts.php&#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;

        &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;//Create a backup
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;copy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$originalFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$backupFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;

        &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;//Overwrite the config file
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;copy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$customFontFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$originalFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;#### truncated_code ####
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;cp&quot;&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;file-composerjson&quot;&gt;file: &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;composer.json&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-javascript&quot; data-lang=&quot;javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;cm&quot;&gt;/**** truncated_code ****/&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;scripts&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;err&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;post-install-cmd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;err&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;App\\Console\\Installer::postInstall&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;post-autoload-dump&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;err&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;Cake\\Composer\\Installer\\PluginInstaller::postAutoloadDump&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;App\\Console\\Installer::postAutoloadDump&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;cm&quot;&gt;/**** truncated_code ****/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;footnotes&quot;&gt;
  &lt;ol&gt;
    &lt;li id=&quot;fn:mpdf-change-font&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Changing fonts in mPDF &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mpdf/mpdf#fonts&quot;&gt;https://github.com/mpdf/mpdf#fonts&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:mpdf-change-font&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li id=&quot;fn:post-autoload-dump&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Composer documentation on &lt;a href=&quot;https://getcomposer.org/doc/articles/scripts.md&quot;&gt;scripts&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:post-autoload-dump&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content>
 </entry>
 
 <entry>
   <title>ui-select broken with AngularJS 1.5.0</title>
   <link href="/ui-select-broken-angular-1.5"/>
   <updated>2016-02-11T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
   <id>/ui-select-broken-angular-1.5</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I recently upgraded my AngularJS app to v1.5.0 and it broke my &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-select&quot;&gt;ui-select&lt;/a&gt; with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext&quot; data-lang=&quot;plaintext&quot;&gt;Error: [ui.select:transcluded] Expected 1 .ui-select-match but got &#39;0&#39;.
    at http://kinwealth.dev/libs/ui-select/select.min.js:7:2362
    at http://kinwealth.dev/libs/ui-select/select.min.js:7:16268
    at http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:17269
    at http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:19883
    at K.d (http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:18237)
    at j (http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:21046)
    at http://kinwealth.dev/libs/ui-select/select.min.js:7:16079
    at ga (http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:28917)
    at s (http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:22226)
    at http://kinwealth.dev/scripts/vendor.5d896021.js:4:26565 &amp;lt;div class=&quot;ui-select-container ui-select-multiple ui-select-bootstrap dropdown form-control&quot; ng-class=&quot;{open: $select.open}&quot; ng-model=&quot;vm.client.users&quot; theme=&quot;bootstrap&quot; ng-disabled=&quot;disabled&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upon searching the internet, the workaround is pretty simple as pointed out by &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/angular-ui/ui-select/issues/1325#issuecomment-160922087&quot;&gt;llafuente&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Add class to ui-select-match and ui-select-choices with the same name&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So all I did was add the class &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;ui-select-match&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;ui-select-choices&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;ui-select-match&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;ui-select-choices&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tags respectively.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
 </entry>
 
 <entry>
   <title>Using same github repository for Yeoman Jekyll's source and dist</title>
   <link href="/source-master-github-pages-repo"/>
   <updated>2015-09-22T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
   <id>/source-master-github-pages-repo</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;In My post on installing and configuring &lt;a href=&quot;/yo-jekyll/&quot;&gt;Jekyll with Yeoman&lt;/a&gt;, I mentioned about using &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;dist&lt;/code&gt; directory to publish for GitHub pages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s the thing&lt;/strong&gt;: I want to be able to track my source code too (to save drafts, posts etc, without publishing)!
 I could use a completely separate git repository (for example myblog_source),
but I wanted to have them all in the same repository. So, here is How I got that done (replace username with your GitHub username).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; /path/to/your/blog
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git add .
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git commit -m &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;first source code commit.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git remote add origin https://github.com/username/username.github.io.git
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git push -u origin master:source
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git checkout &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;source
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;blog$ &lt;/span&gt;git branch -d master&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;git push -u origin master:source&lt;/code&gt; renames the branch to ‘source’ before pushing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: If you already have setup &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;dist&lt;/code&gt; to the master branch, skip the steps below&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;dist
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;dist$ &lt;/span&gt;git init
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;dist$ &lt;/span&gt;git add .
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;dist$ &lt;/span&gt;git commit -m &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;first gh-pages commit&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;dist$ &lt;/span&gt;git remote add origin https://github.com/username/username.github.io.git
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;dist$ &lt;/span&gt;git push -u origin master&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This way you have two completely separate branches &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;source&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;master&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
 </entry>
 
 <entry>
   <title>AWS S3 Access From Specific IPs</title>
   <link href="/aws-s3-ip-access"/>
   <updated>2015-09-21T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
   <id>/aws-s3-ip-access</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;By default accounts are restricted from accessing S3 unless they have been given access via policy.
However, S3 is designed by default to allow any IP address access.
So to block IP’s you would have to specify denies explicitly in the policy instead of allows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A great blog post that help me with setting up restricted access to AWS S3 directory&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
 </entry>
 
 <entry>
   <title>Yo Jekyll - my blogging platform</title>
   <link href="/yo-jekyll"/>
   <updated>2015-09-20T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
   <id>/yo-jekyll</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I have been hearing and seeing developer &amp;amp; enthusiasts use Jekyll&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:JKSITE&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:JKSITE&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;, but never had a chance to check it out - until now!
 And I must say that I love the concept, simplicity and git. It sure does take some time to understand Jekyll, but in the end its all worth the effort!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;a-basic-jekyll-site&quot;&gt;A Basic Jekyll Site&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On researching and looking at various blogs patronizing Jekyll &amp;amp; the cool-new way of blogging, I wanted to give it a shot.
 I initially started off with testing a basic Jekyll blog using&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;gem install jekyll
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;jekyll new my-awesome-site
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;my-awesome-site
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;my-awesome-site$ &lt;/span&gt;jekyll serve&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This popped up a basic site on &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;http://localhost:4000&lt;/code&gt;. And I already feel so good! The same feeling when I endorsed LaTeX&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:LATEX&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:LATEX&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I generally started reading more on Jekyll and how concepts like &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;_posts&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;pages&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;templates&lt;/code&gt;, etc. works.
 Then I stumbled upon a post by David Calhoun&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:DC&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:DC&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;,
 on using Yeoman&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:YO&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#fn:YO&quot; class=&quot;footnote&quot;&gt;4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; a.k.a &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Yo&lt;/code&gt;, a web scaffolding tool that helps you kickstart a project with Jekyll. Things just got interesting!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its not very tough to kickstart a Jekyll blog using Yeoman:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;install-jekyll-with-yeoman&quot;&gt;Install Jekyll with Yeoman&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;npm install -g yo
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;npm install -g generator-jekyllrb
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;mkdir ~/Sites/myblog &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$_&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;myblog~$ &lt;/span&gt;yo jekyllrb&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These were some of my responses to the generator:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;wire-tools-and-preprocessors&quot;&gt;Wire tools and preprocessors.&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;? CSS preprocessor: Compass
? Use Autoprefixer? Yes
? Javascript preprocessor: None&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;choose-a-template&quot;&gt;Choose a template.&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;? Site template: Default Jekyll&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;choose-deployment-options&quot;&gt;Choose deployment options.&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;? Use grunt-build-control &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for &lt;/span&gt;deployment? No&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;building--generating-your-site&quot;&gt;Building &amp;amp; Generating your site&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;grunt serve&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This builds (creates a static version of the source code that you have) and creates a server to view the website at &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;http://localhost:3000&lt;/code&gt;.
 The best part here is that Yo comes with &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.browsersync.io&quot;&gt;Browsersync&lt;/a&gt; - and that is awesome!
 I spent some more time playing around with the platform and started to get a hang of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;deploying-your-site&quot;&gt;Deploying your site&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to see the html generated page of your site use the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot; data-lang=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;gp&quot;&gt;~$ &lt;/span&gt;grunt build&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This generates the HTML code of your site at &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;dist&lt;/code&gt; folder&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;theming&quot;&gt;Theming&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I embrace simple design (as much as I can) and started looking for themes to help me get started.
&lt;a href=&quot;http://lanyon.getpoole.com&quot;&gt;Lanyon&lt;/a&gt;, a theme based on &lt;a href=&quot;http://getpoole.com&quot;&gt;Poole&lt;/a&gt; was an obvious winner! :)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;publishing&quot;&gt;Publishing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All is well, but what about hosting your blog?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The contents / files in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;dist&lt;/code&gt; directory are static HTML pages and can be hosted via &lt;a href=&quot;https://pages.github.com&quot;&gt;GitHub Pages&lt;/a&gt; - best part is it’s free :)
 Simply follow the steps &amp;amp; you have your website up &amp;amp; running!&lt;/p&gt;

